text:
the farm is an ideal school for little boys.
.
on the farm physical strength is directed at nurturing, leadership is directed at making life better for other creatures, drive is directed at competing against daylight or the elements to accomplish a task.
.
part of the reason i am homeschooling is so that ozzie can have more time outside, but i also get the chance to emphasize tenderness through activities like caring for a bummer lamb and tending plants. the farm is a fantastic place to hit home lessons like being aware of how another person/creature is feeling and doing something to make their life better.
.
drivenness and testosterone are not something to fear in growing boys, if we as parents have laid the groundwork for self-awareness and gentleness that will help them mitigate their impulses and direct their energy toward empowering others. i’m trying to do that with my boys by raising the kids to do all the farm chores for me! 😂

text:
i had the brilliant experience over the last couple of days filming with this remarkable lady — hanaa — a 27yr old generation, blade and rotor engineer, and project manager working in #dammam on saudi’s east coast. hanaa gets up at 4.45am, sends her three children off to school, then heads to work for 6am. 2 months ago hanaa had to wait for her driver to get to work. today, hanaa can sit behind the wheel, allowing this busy and fierce woman to define her own schedule. hanaa’s day finishes once she has fed her little ones, helped them with their homework, and prepared the meals for the following day. 
hanaa lives 90minutes away from her work and when she applied for the job hr asked how she would get to work everyday as she wasn’t allowed to drive — ‘just hire me’ hanaa said — ‘i’ll work the getting to work bit out’. hanaa was hired and had to spend half her salary on a driver. but she made it work. 
this magnificent woman had a contagious energy that i rarely experience. a cultural pioneer in her own country that has a long way to go, but is very slowly heading in a direction that may offer more of a choice to hanaa’s little girl. #saudiarabia @courageous_studio #metoo

text:
“find our sisters.” now, more than ever, we as women need to cast aside our differences and stand with one another as we face the force that has been suppressing and segregating us for centuries; patriarchy. 
dating back to the salem witch trials, this construct has had women living in fear of not only speaking up about crimes committed against them, but to even live and speak their individual truths without fear of scrutiny or prosecution. 
patriarchy surfaced when christianity became the predominant religion amoungst european americans (mainly the idea of the man being the head of the home, the brains, the money maker, the authority). some women didn’t want to be demoted to the role of “the wife” and lived independently. they had land and businesses of their own and were well known healers, doctors, and midwives in their communities until the christian men realized that these women were a threat to their power, control, and access to resources that they wanted all to themselves.
[tell a man in power that he can’t have something and watch how quickly he kicks and screams until it’s his]
in order for the christian men to claim back what they believed was “rightfully theirs,” they demonized these woman; exclaiming that their rebelliousness was none other than satan himself posessing them to go against the word of the lord. so clearly (?) the christian thing to do was have a mass genocide of all women (and supporting men) who wanted to live an independent life outside of the christian constructs and patriarchal ideals, whom they called witches. they were typically women who were scene alone or in groups singing and dancing, creating art, speaking to animals, perfecting herblore, and so on. someone could simply say, “i think my neighboor is a witch, she has a cat,” and that alone was enough for execution.
...the legal killings and crimes against women may have stopped, but the fear and suppression that the women of salem felt back in 1692 are still felt to this day; especially in cases like christine blasey ford’s. in my opinion, she is a pioneer in the woman’s rights/empowerment/metoo movement. (cont.)⬇️

text:
thank you aubrey--my master yoda
.
what i love about aubrey is that despite being a guy, he’s in so many ways a bigger feminist than i. one day, when i sent him vidoes of a fitness model doing a challenging routine, he told me i had done better.
.
"don’t go by the way she looks. go by what’s on the inside,” aubrey scolded me. think about the classes we do together. or record them for yourself and see.”
.
“i know what you mean, but i would love to look like her.” i protested.
.
“i like training people with real bodies, real lives, and real schedules. people like you. i don’t train people who have 5 hours in a day, only to exercise. if i think you can do it, trust me you can.”
.
master yoda had spoken and this time i didn’t have any excuses.
.
.
.

.

.

text:
honestly, i'm really not enjoying this pendulum swing. i'm having a hard time seeing all men being vilified. please don't misunderstand, an awakening needs to happen. i know what it's like. i'm a woman in this crazy world and #metoo. i'm no stranger to sexual assault, eventhough i'm choosing to keep my stories to myself for now.
.
but i am also choosing to value, uplift and encourage the amazing men in my life who would never dream of doing anything other than what's respectful and loving. it's not in their dna to do otherwise. 
so here's to you, you all know who you are 💜♂️♀️☮️
#imstillafeminist #yesibelieveinequalrights #yesilovemen #andwomentoo #beanexample
name: Janis Beke
tweet_full:

.
but i am also choosing to value, uplift and encourage the amazing men in my life who would never dream of doing anything other than what's respectful and loving. it is not in their dna to do otherwise. 
so here's to you, you all know who you are 💜♂️♀️☮️

text:
i’ve never posted about my political views, feminism, racism, the me too movement or the most recent dr. ford/kavanaugh hearing.
.
i don’t feel like i have anything intelligent to say or add to be honest.  i also don’t want to say the wrong thing or offend anyone.
.
i don’t pay attention to politics or the news. i don’t even have cable.  i feel like ignorance is bliss and this way i don’t get angry, sad or feel dumb in conversations.
.
but lately i feel i’m doing a disservice to myself and women around me by not showing up and paying attention.
.
i watched the hearing last week and i felt like i was watching reality tv!  i had so many feelings swirling from sad to angry to wtf!  i wanted to see dr. ford’s testimony and wow she was vulnerable and unbelievably brave.
.
i can’t ignore the energy i’ve felt the past couple weeks.  seeing the online posts, and hearing from friends and clients who have been victims of sexual assault and abuse has been heartbreaking.
.
i’ve also started to reflect on my own experiences.  there is one encounter that comes up that didn’t feel good. but i consented and went along so it’s my own fault right?! all i know is that i didn’t enjoy it, i wasn’t sure what was happening in the moment, i felt used and icky after and it’s not what i wanted.
.
as a type a extrovert that leans towards more masculine energy,  i’m focusing on nourishing my feminine energy lately so there’s no coincidence why i’m feeling all this more and felt called to share.  i can’t ignore the collective energy anymore.
.
this post feels scary and vulnerable to share but ummm head shake!...what about the women that have suffered assault and abuse that are coming forward and sharing (or not sharing). i can’t even imagine what this feels like for them.  this share was the least i could do.
.
interestingly enough, i was inspired to post this by 2 men i follow online.  they didn’t know what to say but knew they wanted to show up and speak up more.  if they were brave enough to speak up as men, then i needed to speak up as a woman.
.
i commit to paying more attention.  i also offer my time and my heart to anyone that needs a safe place to feel heard, loved and supported. ❤

text:
long post alert!!! rocking my purple for domestic violence awareness!!! i get chills thinking about how i was called to do this work in my mother's womb. i was born in february. ameythst is my birthstone and violet is the flower for the month. i was named yolanda which means violet. my parents just liked the name.  only recently did my mother know what it meant! purple is the color for domestic violence awareness! 
everything i went through was so i could know what victims go through, first hand. because i was a victim. i believe i may have saved a couple lives because i have never hesitated to call the police when i saw a woman being beat down right in front of me. i once stood toe to toe with an abuser who knew i was about to call the police on him. i didn't have a phone back then. i was trying to get to a payphone. i went in my house snuck out the back door and called the police. 
then, my sister became a victim. we tried to save her but we couldn't. i promised at her funeral i would do the best i could to prevent the horror she endured and the devastation my family experienced as a result of her murder.

it's not a path i would have chosen for myself. it's not a popular topic. it's often frustrating. i have to relive the pain over and over again. but, knowing your purpose is an amazing feeling!!!
what the devil means for harm god has a plan for good all the time! i can't wait to see what god has in store next, not just for me but for all those i am divinely connected to! what a mighty god we serve!!! #imasurvivor #purpleismypassion
#imsurvivor #silentnomore #domesticviolencesurvivor #domesticabuse #intimatepartnerabuse #intimatepartnerviolence #metoo #domesticviolence #octoberisdomesticviolenceawarenessmonth #breakthesilence

text:
i am not your f*cking clown-----ink on paper. 8x10 inches. .

this is how i feel when women are ridiculed by presidents after they finally have the guts to speak out about sexual assault. .

trump carries on about how sexual assault accusers ruin careers of men, but how many careers have been ruined for women because of sexual assault? how many times has a woman's entire sense of place and self been totally obliterated by a man who used her body for his own pleasure without her permission? we need to shed light on the effects of sexual assault-- the latent effects, the obvious effects, the not-so-obvious effects. our bodies carry the trauma for years. you want to talk about loss? let's talk about loss... into every job, every relationship, everything. we carry the burden and the trauma. but hey, make fun, you fucking ape. sure. go ahead. it will only ever be a joke to some. that is how much a woman is worth to some. that is how it feels to be a woman in this world.

text:
embrace change. sometimes it has to get ugly to fully change and transform. we are all being called to heal from our sexual trauma based on what is happening in the media and in politics. it is time to speak out about what happened to you. nearly every woman i know has been sexually assaulted or close to it. we have to bring attention to this horrible issue so that it can be resolved and brought to light. it is not fun, brings up buried feelings that are painful and creates new feelings as people justify the behavior and make excuses for those who sexually abuse. what a mess. we will move from this place smarter, lighter and with a greater voice. .
.
.

do we dare to judge the streetwalker?

text:
“i am here today not because i want to be. i am terrified. i am here because i believe it is my civic duty to tell you what happened to me while brett kavanaugh and i were in high school.” “i tried to yell for help. when i did, brett put his hand over my mouth to stop me from screaming. this was what terrified me the most, and has had the most lasting impact on my life. it was hard for me to breathe, and i thought that brett was accidentally going to kill me.” “indelible in the hippocampus is the laughter, the uproarious laughter between the two, and their having fun at my expense.”
- dr. christine blasey ford

i’m in dc marching today. if you can’t march call your senators: (202) 224-3121. 
brett kavanaugh is a serial abuser. as a justice on our nation’s highest court, he will have the power to enact that abuse on a national scale, rolling back the rights women have worked for a generation to secure. that can’t happen on our watch. we’re marching in dc to remind every senator that women. are. watching.

we have a real chance to change the course of history. we have a real chance to show that abuse will no longer be rewarded with even more power. we have a real chance to win this. get involved: cancelkavanaugh.com

if anyone recalls the #centralpark5 5 
trump's apparent concern for innocent young men was further complicated by his own record of having falsely accused five young men in the now infamous central park jogger case in new york city in 1989.

in one of his earliest forays into the political arena, trump took out a full-page ad in several newspapers about the case, and demanded that lawmakers "bring back the death penalty. bring back our police!" "i want to hate these muggers and murderers," trump wrote in the text of the ad. "they should be forced to suffer and, when they kill, they should be executed for their crimes." the five young men who were convicted of the crime, and who trump had called on the state to execute, were later exonerated using dna evidence.

now with his #supremecourt nominee, #brettkavanaugh its a different story. what are your thoughts? 
#centralpark #donaldtrump #sexualassualt #factoftheday #gossipingheifers #newyorkcity #youngmen #metoo

text:
i was one of those women that thought years ago that #girlpower was just a thing that gave women something to do. i was foolish enough to believe that as nation...: a world, we have grown and developed and that gender bias and violence against women were not really a thing. i believed that women were given equal opportunities..... until i was exposed and then started paying attention and having my own experiences of all of the above. i am going to take some time to share facts.... all are documented and can be researched so go look and see for yourself! 
so many of us have these experiences and we don't share because we are embarrassed or we feel foolish. when just one  is bold enough to share we realize how many have had a similar experience. our girls need to know that is is not ok. some of us blame ourselves and stay in abusive relationships.... it is not ok! we have to break the cycle and we can only do that by being empowered with knowledge, a community and standing up for what we know is right.
i encounter women and girls too often who think that using their body for financial gain is ok, as a matter of fact it seems to be the norm now. 
fathers telling their daughters at 13 and 15 that they are big enough now to go and sell themselves to contribute or take care of themselves.... #knowyourworth #togethernesswins #heforshe #metoo #winwin #wakeup #staywoke

text: it’s amazing to see a movement happening where, instead of tearing each other down, people are supporting each other. it just goes to show, nothing gets accomplished when we wander through the world unaware of others’ struggles. in a political environment of fear mongers, hate speeches, and ignorance, women and their supporters are rising up to remind each other of their inner strength and that is a beautiful thing. i have seen so many women sharing their stories and helping each other heal. this piece i created, was in the spirit of this. i wanted it to show the raw power of a woman when pushed beyond the limits of what she can accept and, also represent the connection beyond race and religion we have to each other. together we are truly a force to be reckoned with, a force for change. thank you, to so many spearheading this movement. thank you from me and from my daughter, who, because she is only 8 yrs old, knows nothing of the evils in the world but will hopefully enjoy a better world for your efforts and honesty. i can’t tag everyone but these are just some amazingly strong women, period. keep fighting and we will all do the same in your wake. @milano_alyssa  @natalieportman @elizabethwarren @padmalakshmi @debimazar #women #metoo #art #metoomovement #empowerment #politicalart #womensvoices #strongertogether #digitalart #befierce #resist #nastywomenvote #artistsoninstagram #artistsofinstagram #mydaughtersfuture #thankyou #artoninstagram #artofinstagram

text: as i'm watching the news this morning hearing all about the kavanaugh case, i see that connie chung wrote christine ford a letter about her own sexual assault that happened many years ago. i read the letter and it really resonated with me. speaking from experience because i have been sexually assaulted before, sometimes you don't remember all the details as far as dates and times but, you do remember the way you were feeling. as much as you wish you didn't remember it's seared into your memory. i'm disgusted by the way our president has mocked dr. ford about not remembering minor details about her assault. it's so wrong. for anyone who has ever been a victim of sexual assault, i urge you to read connie chung's letter to dr. ford. know that you are not alone and you should never feel afraid. #metoo

text:
t o d a y.
sharing the fierce, yet loving wisdom of one of the l spot's most cherished intuitives @northern.lights.witch :
:
#metoo #metoomovement #timesup #sexualabuse #sexualassault #cancelkavanaugh #ibelieveher #believesurvivors #scalesofjustice #justice :
@regran_ed from @northern.lights.witch -  libra season
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i'm late on our wisdom for libra season, but this can serve as a good midway point check in. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
libra is all about beauty, charm, and balance. this sign is a balm of idealism after practical virgo. because this is all about balance, i was not at all surprised when i pulled a 2. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the 2 of swords is interesting - all of the twos are about duality and balance, but the 2 of swords speaks to me of the need to be rooted in the external world while looking inward with your inner eye. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this month, find a balance in your emotions. if you are a survivor of sexual assault and/or abuse, you may be feeling triggered by this vicious news cycle. sometimes, our response is to bury ourselves, to put on our blindfolds and retreat. but this can often lead to a certain constriction. in our panic to be away from it all, we end up focusing on the "all" we are trying to get away from. we may lash out, because we are trying so hard not to feel our feelings that they take us over. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
libra season is all about balance, finding beauty, but recognizing the ugly. it is also about justice - the scales. if you try to hide from your feelings, they control you. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
trust your inner guides, trust that your emotions are telling you something. you have a deep psychic well, and if you explore it you will find the tools to persevere.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

libra is all about beauty, charm, and balance. this sign is a balm of idealism after practical virgo. because this is all about balance, i was not at all surprised when i pulled a 2. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the 2 of swords is interesting - all of the twos are about duality and balance, but the 2 of swords speaks to me of the need to be rooted in the external world while looking inward with your inner eye. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this month, find a balance in your emotions. if you are a survivor of sexual assault and/or abuse, you may be feeling triggered by this vicious news cycle. sometimes, our response is to bury ourselves, to put on our blindfolds and retreat. but this can often lead to a ceain constriction. in our panic to be away from it all, we end up focusing on the "all" we are trying to get away from. we may lash out, because we are trying so hard not to feel our feelings that they take us over. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
libra season is all about balance, finding beauty, but recognizing the ugly. it is also about justice - the scales. if you try to hide from your feelings, they control you. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
trust your inner guides, trust that your emotions are telling you something. you have a deep psychic well, and if you explore it you will find the tools to persevere.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

content ⚠️ warning: sexual assault, brett kavanaugh
.
.
.
.
.
#whyididntreport: because i was afraid, ashamed, embarrassed. because i didn’t know what was happening to me. because i thought it was my fault. because he threatened and manipulated me. because when i finally did try to report, i was told that it wasn’t worth my time and that i was overreacting. i was silenced. 
last week, professor christine blasey ford became a hero. she told her story of sexual assault in front of a group of people who didn’t want to believe her, just as professor anita hill did 27 years ago. today, because of their bravery, thousands of survivors feel empowered to share their stories too. i wish i could write more, but this past week has been really emotionally exhausting. just remember that if you yourself are not a survivor of assault, it’s highly likely someone close to you is. so please be a little extra nice to people the next few days. you never know who is struggling with the after effects of abuse, and it’s an extra touchy subject right now, so send lots of love and hold space for those around you ❤️ and to all survivors everywhere, i am so proud of you. i am here for you and i believe you. they can’t keep doing this to us. #christineblaseyford #anitahill #brettkavanaugh #stopkavanaugh #kavanope #ibelieveher #believesurvivors #metoo @whyididntreportit

text:
inktober day four: i forgive you.

i forgive you for finding others that seemed better than our hangouts. 
i forgive you for cheating on me; she was probably the better option anyway. 
i forgive you for replacing me, your old best friend, for your current; they probably made you laugh harder anyway. 
i forgive you for hitting me, repeatedly. i don’t care anymore if it was something i said, a mistake i made that i didn’t register, or if you just had a bad day. 
i forgive you for leaving me after i gave you my paycheck that week to make sure you were ok.
i forgive you for blocking me, unadding me on social media, and then you would talk about me behind my back. 
i forgive you for taking advantage of my “let me fix this” personality and using up my time, patience and energy. it showed me that i need to be careful who i give that energy to. 
i forgive you for leading me on and then calling me a sin once you regretted it. 
there are so many more that i need to type out to forgive, but i just forgive you. not because you deserve it. but because i don’t deserve to wonder what i did wrong and how could i fix it. not everyone deserves my can-do attitude of trying to create a compromise or even just lose the battle; because i valued them and the relationship more than my need to win. so i forgive you. because i deserve to not have this weight on my shoulders anymore. 
i forgive you, and i forgive myself for being so hard on myself for this long. i forgive me. and i forgive you, but you don’t deserve it. 
i just want to breathe. and in order to breathe, you don't just inhale, but exhale too; i'm finally releasing this.

i forgive you for leaving me after i gave you my paycheck that week to make sure you were ok.
i forgive you for blocking me, unadding me on social media, and then you would talk about me behind my back. 
i forgive you for taking advantage of my “let me fix this” personality and using up my time, patience and energy. it showed me that i need to be careful who i give that energy to. 
i forgive you for leading me on and then calling me a sin once you regretted it. 
there are so many more that i need to type out to forgive, but i just forgive you. not because you deserve it. but because i don’t deserve to wonder what i did wrong and how could i fix it. not everyone deserves my can-do attitude of trying to create a compromise or even just lose the battle; because i valued them and the relationship more than my need to win. so i forgive you. because i deserve to not have this weight on my shoulders anymore. 
i forgive you, and i forgive myself for being so hard on myself for this long. i forgive me. and i forgive you, but you don’t deserve it. 
i just want to breathe. and in order to breathe, you do not just inhale, but exhale too; i am finally releasing this.

text:
ceilings - (1/3) there’s a wonderful story in the new testament recorded in luke 5:17-26 that i read yesterday morning and i saw in a new way in light of current events.  in the story, jesus is teaching and some men want to bring their paralyzed friend to him to be healed.  because of the crowds that are surrounding jesus, they are unable to get to him.  so, they decide to climb up on the roof, open up the tiles on the roof (i don’t know whether they literally destroyed part of the roof or whether it was easy to remove and then replace them) to make a hole big enough to lower their friend down to jesus.  what follows is an interchange between jesus, the friends, the man and the religious leaders about healing, about forgiveness of sin, and about healing on the sabbath.

but what got me thinking in a new direction about this story was a comment made in another context yesterday when i was listening to a podcast called the liturgists.  one of the hosts shared that “just as the gospel can be used to oppress, so it can be used to liberate.” this was in part of a discussion of the ways that christianity has not lived up to it’s core actions of love and grace.

just as the gospel can be used to oppress, so it can be used to liberate.  #metoo #justice #equality #freedom

text:
17yr-old lashonda childs had a job, owned a business, looked after her family, and went back to school to continue her education. she was beautiful and vivacious, but, just two days shy of her 18th birthday, she was murdered by a 28yr-old man who would not take "no" for an answer. *
*
no matter the gender, if someone says—or shows—that they do not want to sleep with you, date you, see you or communicate with you, your next move needs to be to respect that and move on. no one owes themselves to us. *
*
no one deserves to die in this manner, and no family deserves this degree of suffering. the entitlement of men, especially, is sickening. check on your friends and check your problematic friends.
*
*

text:
recited: a call to action 🔥
yes. that was my face when at 16 a stranger grabbed my vulva in a public space. utter disgust. and every damn time i hear of another person who was molested, raped or sexually abused i feel that rage again.
through the process of healing i learnt that we must share our stories. not for anybody else, but us. when we’re ready, under our own terms. otherwise, the rage, fear and sorrow is stored in our bodies. and it drives our lives.
but that anger, when healed, becomes power. when we speak our truth, we claim it back. watch us sew our pieces back to wholeness. there is no stopping us!
to read full story, check my bio! 🧡

text:
my name is alexandra.
i love chipotle, photography, fitness, laughing, dogs, and short walks on the beach (because i'd rather sit and roll around in one spot).
thank you all for the support, softness, stories, and love. i'm overwhelmed at the feedback i've received.
i shared my *condensed* experience not because i wanted to, but because i needed to. for the women who are unable to, and for you all to hear a voice of someone you know.
1 out of 5 women are sexually assaulted. 1 out of 33 men are sexually assaulted. these are someone's daughters/sons, sisters/brothers, mothers/fathers, wife/husband, friend, neighbor. have awareness, have openness to other perspectives, be kind to everyone around you.
i shared my story so that those of you who have also been assaulted, dont feel alone. you did nothing wrong. you said nothing wrong. you wore nothing wrong. it can happen to anyone. 7 out of 10 rapes, the victim knows the perpetrator. i knew mine. do not let them take away your worth. do not let them feel as though you dont matter. you are important, your potential still remains after the fact. you are capable, you are strong. you are intelligent, you are beautiful. you are loved, and you will continue to be.
if you feel like no one cares or no one wants to listen, i do. i care, i'll listen to you. i've already recieved countless messages from women about their stories and courage. i'm grateful, so grateful to hear you.
key point: please dont let the cruelty of others define you or destroy you. i've done so for 6 years. transform your pain into passion. im still struggling, i'm still rebuilding, but i've began to look at my life and not only see the ash, but the beauty i've created. i dont have a perfect life, i dont have anything handed to me. i work hard but i now get to choose what my existence is about.
i hope to become a physical trainer and photographer, i also hope to travel and have a dog soon. i hope to learn spanish. i hope to be happy. i hope to live a life with meaning, i hope to help others. notice the little miracles in your day. enjoy yourself, dont let these chains weigh you down forever, youll miss out on a delightful life. thank you all for listening❤

text_retweet:
@regran_ed from @anidifranco -  goddess bless dr. ford, ana maria archila
and all women who stand up and speak out.
and check out this inspiring video from @gracieandrachel!
-ani 
link to full video in bio.
#repost @gracieandrachel
・・・
her
———
on the morning of thursday, september 27th, 2018, an eager anticipation woke us up in our brooklyn loft unusually early. with our hearts racing, we tuned into the hearings of dr. christine blasey ford and judge brett kavanaugh.
———
amidst dr. ford’s emotionally brave testimony, kavanaugh’s flippant denial, and an amalgamation of statements from an assembly of both incredibly compassionate and unbelievably ruthless senators, we made a new song. and it was for her.
———
once the hearings were over, we began putting a video together to more fully capture the inspiration behind this song. we wanted to point to women, from a range of walks of life, women who have taken a stance when it wasn’t necessarily easy to do so. our goal was to highlight the courage it takes to call something out loud and to stand up tall when the odds may not be in our favor.
———
the women in this piece are just a few among many who inspire us to continue to use our voices and demand to be heard. the conclusory chorus lyric “never look back again” doesn’t imply we shouldn’t look back on the women who have taught us how to lead the way — we most absolutely should — but that we should always move bravely into the future. we hope with our song to thank the women who have empowered us so selflessly and perhaps to inspire those still searching to find their strengths.
———
see the full video for “her” now! link in bio.
———

i declare new relationships, marriages, love, affection, children being born, and unprecedented romance in the body of christ...
,,,because men are stepping up...
...not mistreating and abusing women... but walking off with the gates!

text:
@thegridbeatsstrong for the image prompt by @yiki_draws 
#freethegrid #yourheartbeatsstrong 
and so the scrolls 
from ancient times
have been released.
the vessel, which trapped 
her magic for centuries,
now open by the strokes
of greedy hands.
she emerges, 
in waves of indignation,
taking form, as artwork,
sculpted by the gods
with the finest details
to the curves of her beauty.
her head tilts up to the sky,
which greets her home.
she is free 
from man’s restraint.

text:
dear john,
so here i sit stunned and taken by surprise, crying like a baby, like i didn't recognize the look in your eyes. i blame myself every time. you walk and pace across the room, blaming me for something that i didn't do. heaven forbid that you see some blood, you tuck your tail like a coward and run. and then you want to show me real love? i stiffen with every touch. it scares me that you love me this much. i know it's your power over me that gets you off. i don't know which one of us is the flame, or which one of us is the moth. so here i go again playing the fool, for the things you do. you start with your insinuations. i'm reluctant to talk back, feeling a multitude of hesitations. your voice is sharp, your words slicing my heart like a knife. i'm sick of playing nice! in the midst of all your rage, you slapped me across my face. i'm like a sitting duck, locked in a cage. i can no longer play this game! i'm done! i will no longer love a clown. i will no longer let you put me down! i have called the police, and pressed all charges. your clothes i donated to the salvation army. the locks are changed. i don't even know your name. forget mine just the same. i'm through with all of your demons. i won't even pray for you, i'll pray for me, and all of my seasons! i will no longer try to understand your reasons.
you say you're tired of the shit i do? yeah, me too!
image by @cbrown_art for @inktober
poem by @robingk81
#metoo

#theilluminatedauthors #artofexpression #standup #saynomore #domesticviolence #nomore #sexualassault #cbart #inktober #robingk81 #femalepoet #art #poetry #fromtheheart #bittersweet

text:
en septiembre han sido 13 las mujeres asesinadas por violencia machista.
•
mejor ni pensemos en cuantas van a lo largo del año, porque sería terrorífico.
•
¿por qué no le damos importancia a este hecho? ¿por qué no le damos la relevancia que tiene? ¿por qué no nos preocupamos más? ¿por qué se pasa por alto? ¿por qué nadie hace nada?
•
yo tengo mis propias respuestas... si queréis compartir las vuestras, debatimos en comentarios.

text:
this was dr ford's response when asked what the most vivid memory was of her experience of assault. her response speaks not only to the humiliation that survivors so often experience, but also to her psychology background, as she references the part of the brain that is responsible for memory storage. for this traumatic experience to then be perpetuated by the president of the united states, at a rally where he mocked her and encouraged the audience to laugh at her, really illustrates why so many victims don't report that experience. i want to see men in power standing up for the experiences of survivors, and passionately and angrily defending their right to safety and respect.
.
in my practice room, i believe survivors. i don't laugh. this isn't funny. and we should all be angry about the culture that has been created, where survivors across the world are being re-traumatised by seeing dr ford mocked by one of the most powerful men in the world. .
survivors, please know that there are lots of people resisting this culture. lots of people, myself included, who are dedicated to holding safe spaces for your rage, your fear, your grief, and your healing.
.

text:
how much is a girl worth? (new post link in bio ✨
••••••••••••••••••••••
why are we speaking out now? why are there are so many voices coming forward? some people want to take the easy way out and brush it off as what ‘boys do’ or say it is because ‘women lie’, but those are bullshit excuses. so many of us are speaking now because we saw our mothers and grandmothers silenced. we saw them live in a world where their truth did not matter and it ate away at them slowly. we see them continue to struggle with those horrific events and yet never be taken seriously. we have seen our friends deal with the lasting negative effects of their sexual assault or we have faced it ourselves. we are tired of living in a constant state of fear or asking ourselves what we can do to prevent an assault. we are tired of the fear of walking alone at night, watching our drinks, and second guessing what we wear. we are done asking for the country and the world to see us as valuable and demanding that our experiences be heard. we are angry and it is time that the world heard our collective voice of rage.

republican sen. ben sasse drops a bombshell on the debate over brett kavanaugh's nomination to the supreme court

bryan logan 
oct 3, 2018, 10:17 pm et ￼jim bourg-pool/getty imagessen. ben sasse of nebraska.

republican sen. ben sasse of nebraska gave an impassioned speech on sexual assault and the #metoo movement on the senate floor wednesday night.

sasse also dropped a bombshell about where he stands on brett kavanaugh, president donald trump's second nominee to the supreme court. "i urged the president to nominate a different individual. i urged the president to nominate a woman," sasse said.

he recounted the experiences of two personal friends he said were raped, adding that the #metoo movement has been "complicated," but also a "very good thing." then sasse turned back to trump: "we all know that the president cannot lead us through this time."

text:
as my steps echo off the lonely walls
i reach for my lifeline and i text,
i tell you,
it's 10.43 and i am walking down the alley
silence.
with keys between my fingers
and peppermint breath spray in the other palm
i hurry between the lamplight
silence. 
echo, echo, echo
my footsteps arrogantly giving away my position 
pausing to walk on the balls
soft padding now,
better.
silence. 
lamplight to lamplight
test spraying and mentally playing out my wide foot stance. 
steady as i shout taser taser taser,
providing those vital seconds of confusion,
hesitation,
enough to make a break for safety.
knowing the exact shape of the key fob
the exact one for the exact lock to run inside
glancing over each shoulder a hundred times
breathing to release tension with the empty reflection of the apartment doors
inside the lift door slides shut and i reach for my phone 
silence. 
taunting blank screen.
anger bubbles up inside me, 
i stew red hot now
adrenaline redirected 
how do you not see it?
how can you not understand how it feels?
that getting home alive is not the best case scenario
how can years of night walking male privilege not show the clashing contrast here?
as i show you the crime map of sexual assaults in the mile radius.
silence.
i turn off the lights defeated.
how can you not get it,
i text to put it on record.
i text so when i don't come home
you know i entered that alleyway at 10.43
so you can find the exact moment of cctv with ease,
even in the face of danger,
i am nothing but accommodating. 
but instead we lay in the darkness, soft snores echoing on these safe bedroom walls.
silence.
. 
#poetry #poetrycommunity #poem #poems #poemsofinstagram #poetsofinstagram #safety #woman #night #feminism #werise #metoo #feminist #feministpoetry

text:
be kind to a sexual assault survivor you know today. i urge you to ask how you can support them.
.
in a reality where the us president - an accused abuser himself - publicly mocked and drew laughter about a sexual assault survivor in the same week that the survivor's abuser will be confirmed to the highest court of law in the usa, we're all feeling pretty shitty.
.
i'm so, so tired of watching sex abusers get into high office. it's heartbreaking, and it's honestly really fucked up. most survivors will never get justice for their assaults, but at the very fucking least, you'd think we could actively work to keep abusers out of the white house, the supreme court, and congress.
.
yet here we are.
.
so offer a survivor you know some support today.
.
.
.
.

text:
"she once told a boyfriend about these considerations and he said, 'you are completely out of your mind.' she told a new friend at work and she said, 'honey, you're not crazy. you're a woman.'" difficult women by roxane gay @littlebrown @hachettebooks (2017)

i started this volume of short stories yesterday, and i've already devoured half of it. #roxanegay makes me rage. she makes me rage against a system of social inequalities that allows men to hold power over women's bodies. she makes me rage against the physical injustice of womanhood. she makes me rage on behalf of women i will never know and who may not actually exist because i know their pain.

last week, for #feministfriday and #ourdaughtersdaughterssociety, i posted a photo which had me in it. the support i got from both male and non-male members of the #bookstagramcommunity was incredible. i have had discussions with some of you about the dangers of appearing submissive: easy-prey for sexual predators who tend to target women they consider weak and unlikely to fight back. i fight back. i have always fought back. i have lines of tears burned into my face from where i've fought back. scars from times when i fought back.

the above #quote refers to the considerations women have to make when out alone in the world. the things they have to be careful about, the ways they need to protect themselves from men. until recently, my own partner didn't take me seriously when i explained how commonplace #sexualassault is. so i started to tell him. every. single. time. it. happens. it was strangely validating, but sad, to see his worldview shift. sad, because he feels helpless to protect me. validating, because he sees what i've had to survive to become who i am.

#qotd: have you ever had your gender-based experiences negated or misunderstood? how have you dealt with this?

#iamnotfreewhileanywomanisunfree

#stopvictimblaming

text:
🍭.
.
.
🔸last week, on thursday, i had two bad experiences at a place at which i worked involving two different male customers.👎🏻.
.
.
🔸although i’d rather not get into all that happened, i will say that god provided a way out for me from that particular place. ❤️🙏🏻.
.
.
🔸it was painful to hear that according to the venue’s owner, i have “zero personality” and i “can’t sing”. ⁉️⁉️.
.
.
🔸i am gone from that particular place now and will be trying a new location with an earlier shift and games (!!!) tomorrow. i’m super excited to try this out!! 😁👍🏻😊.
.
.
🔸i must always remember this quote because it is the truth! 💜 i happen to think i have a mega unique 😁 personality. as for that singin remark? who qualified him to be a judge of that?!? i’m not a pop sensation; i’m classically trained. 🎤.
.
.
➡️p.s. — i’m ok with not going there anymore as i had two bad experiences a week ago (same night) at this place. #metoo moments. 👎🏻😔.
.
.
🔸sorry, man. my opinion of me matters more to me than yours. ✔️.
.
.

text: it is hard to believe that it has been over a week since i shared the stage with my fierce friends @joannen.smith & @fatimagossgraves to talk about the gains made by the #metoo & #timesup movements. thank you to the @unfoundation & @mashable for inviting us to join. i also had the immense honor & privilege to participate during the 73rd #unga to talk about the importance of the un global compact for safe, orderly and regular migration. i was the only member of civil society who was invited to speak alongside the un secretary general, president of the general assembly, foreign minister of morocco and the un special representative for international migration. it was a big responsibility. my goal was to center the people who will be directly impacted by the gcm. thank you to hon. loiuse arbour for inviting me to be part of this historic event. it was great to have natalia & monica alonso as my guests, plus thanks to edward for all of his support on the trip.

text:
started by the association of alberta sexual assault services, the #ibelieveyou campaign urges sexual assault victims to speak and encourages people to listen to them.
even though the support for sexual assault survivors shows promise, the prevailing notion that others aren’t willing to listen keeps victims silent and allows perpetrators to reoffend. what this campaign aims at is a shift away from minimizing and justifying sexual assault and towards believing and supporting survivors.

tl;dr: the #metoo campaign has encouraged women to come out and speak up. now, it is time to urge the others to believe them or at the least, listen to them rather than outrightly minimizing the trauma faced by them.

text:
today is the cinnamon bun day! to all my followers that’s not from sweden you maybe didn’t know that we have a tradition here to celebrate sugar in different forms (and i love it 😍) we have våffeldagen (waffle day), semmeldagen (that’s honestly more of a month than a day really) and now the newcomer where we eat a crazy amount of swedish cinnamon buns. i think it’s pretty funny and cozy that a whole country celebrates desserts. and i do think it’s great to get a little more balance in the conversation with all the strict and destructive ideas and images about bodies, food and training. go eat a cinnamon bun and be nice to yourself and to others! your body is perfectly alright as it is. 😊💕
.

text: *what if it was your son* or *aren't you more scared for our sons than our daughters*? nope! for a very long time, what a white man did had many fewer consequences (boys being boys, he's just a kid, well you shouldn't have been wearing that...). slowly it seems like the pendulum is moving and asking these men to be judged by their actions, just like literally everyone else on the planet, and to some men it may seem like something is being taken away, but in reality, this is equity. i am actually much more concerned that my sons are good people and understand their own privilege and the fact that they have no right to anyone's body or property (etc) other than their own, than about the very very very very slim chance that they are wrongfully accused. #metoo #ibelievesurvivors

text: if the one that gave me #metoo was nominated to the supreme court and i saw him on the national news recollecting his name for the first time in nearly three decades this is what now know: i would have called @sensusancollins office and been flown to dc to testify which would have been the beginning of my life being completely destroyed. period. the end. political motives would trump logic and ethics, as i would be unable to answer why i did not report, tell more than one person until my husband, not recall details, not sought therapy and the list goes on. no fbi investigation would support my claims. i would return home defeated, demoralized with my past hurt successfully crushing my once healed heart. so i hold onto hope while praying for truth to be revealed and for those deaf to the heart of this issue to hear. #slowtospeakquicktolisten #truth #mystory

text:
harvey weinstein skandalı üzerinden 1 yıl geçti. bu olayın ardından #metoo diyebilen yüzlerce kadınla başlayan hareket, #economist dergisinin ekim sayısında #sexandpower başlığı altında incelenmiş. taciz, tecavüz, istismar gibi konuların sadece sekse indirgenmemesi gerektiğini, bunun #güç kavramı ve #gücükullanmayla da doğrudan ilgili bir durum olduğunu dergi ayrıntılarıyla incelemiş bu ay. 
bu aralar ben de #kadınvei̇ktidar" konusuna takmıştım; çok iyi geldi bu dosya bana. 6 ekim cumartesi günü #bursanilüferbelediyesi'nde kadın ve iktidar başlıklı bir #yaratıcıokumaveyazma atölyesi yapacağım yetişkinlerle. #tomrisuyar'ın bir öyküsü üzerinden kadın olmayı, #toplumsalcinsiyet kavramını ve iktidarı tartışacağız kadınlarla. i̇ktidarın kadının varlığını yok sayma araçlarını, gücünü kadınlar ve erkekler üzerinde kullanma ve meşrulaştırma yöntemlerini #sanat aracılığıyla düşüneceğiz. #kadınçalışmalarını canım eskişehrimden sonra bursa'da da yapmak heyecan verici. bu yıl vaktim olursa, i̇stanbul'da da buluşalım mı eyy kadınlar? metoo olaylarının azalması ve kadın dayanışmasının artması umuduyla... sanat aracılığıyla bunları konuşabilmek iyi geliyor hepimize, çünkü sanat insanı iyileştiriyor, güzelleştiriyor, hem ruhumuzu hem de dünyayı... i̇yi ki... bunu yapmak için pek fazla seçeneğim de yok zaten. i̇nsanı ve insani olan her şeyi yaşamak ve yaşatmak için sanattan başka bir yol varsa bile ben bilmiyorum... #metoo #womenstudies #creativereadingwritingworkshop #shortstories #powerandwomen #artheals #literatureheals

text_retweet:
#metoo #backacissiwallin
⬇⬇⬇⬇⬇⬇⬇
#repost @ninarungs
・・・
det är svåra tider nu. kanske är ingen förvånad över det som sker nu. mest eftersom det skett så många gånger förut. att kvinnors berättelser såhär ”ett år efter #metoo” åter ifrågasätts. att kvinnorna får höra att de är galna, ute efter pengar, berömmelse eller drivs av hämnd och därför hittar på. allt från hur @uppdraggranskning vinklat ”granskningen” av #metoo till den utpekades fördel, till valet att låta den utpekade sitta hos malou von sivers medan hon som utsatts är bannlyst, till att kvinnor som berättar om övergrepp som trumps föreslagna domare utsatt dom för åter igen misstänkliggörs och utsätts för hån. av en sittande president. det kanske inte är oväntat, men om vi bara skakar på huvudet åt trump, åt alla ifrågasättanden och misstänkliggöranden av kvinnor så normaliseras det. och det får inte hända! då blev inte #metoo den ögonöppnare och revolution som jag menar att den inneburit. och det ska inte de rädda männen ta ifrån oss. inte vår rätt att berätta. inte vår rätt att stå upp mot de övergrepp som män utsatt oss för och inte få vår röst att tystna. historien kommer att visa vilka som stod upp för kvinnor och kvinnors rätt att berätta och se vilka som gjorde allt för att få övergreppen att upphöra. och då vill jag att så många som möjligt står på rätt sida historien. så agera när ni hör misstänkliggöranden av #metoo, av kvinnors berättelser, av idéer som handlar om påhittade motiv för att sätta dit män. agera när någon säger något objektifierande eller sexistiskt. agera när din kompis, kollega eller släkting skämtar på kvinnors bekostnad och agera när du ser att någon går över någons gräms eller när hen inte ens har möjlighet att se sin egen gräns passerad. så kan vi tillsammans stå upp mot farsoten som mäns våld och övergrepp mot kvinnor, barn och icke-binära innebär. ————————————————————————- tack för bilderna @kanon.jon ❤️✊

flera kollegor konstaterade efter träffen att det är fint att få fundera över detta på arbetstid och att det är värdefullt att prata om hur vi är mot varandra på vår arbetsplats.

text:
"i ricordi di quella sera, che mi portano qui oggi, sono scolpiti nella memoria e mi hanno ossessionata in vari momenti della mia vita adulta."
.
christine blasey ford, docente di psicologia all'università di palo alto e ricercatrice di psicologia alla stanford university school of medicine, ha accusato il giudice brett kavanaugh, candidato di donald trump alla corte suprema, di violenza sessuale.
.
un racconto che ricorda centinaia di migliaia di racconti di violenza, di potere, di silenzi che durano decine di anni.
.
alla testimonianza di christine ford, come da programma, sono seguite smentite e dichiarazioni di innocenza. oltre che, per nulla inaspettate, le affermazioni presuntuose dello stesso presidente donald trump, che ha parlato delle accuse della dott. ford come di falsità.
.
intanto, altre donne si fanno avanti, accusando kavanaugh di violenza e molestie. fra queste deborah ramirez, e altre 65 donne, firmatarie di una lettera aperta nella quale si rimarca il comportamento sessualmente molesto del candidato durante il periodo scolastico.per la testimonianza completa 👉 https://goo.gl/ggjnjg

text:
📷 @camilleleage .
« après #metoo, j’aimerais
voir plus de femmes investir l’espace public.
à l’instar d’elsa noyons qui sort régulièrement
sa table de son espace privé et s’installe
là où elle le souhaite. »
.
//// #nuitblanche2018 - 6 octobre //// #femmesphotographes et anis gras, le lieu de l’autre à arceuil, organisent une exposition en lien avec le numéro 4 de la revue.
.
le theme ////
comment se rendre visible ?
comment rendre visible ?
aujourd’hui la notion de visibilité est mise en avant. elle est dotée d’une grande richesse pour penser l’enchevêtrement des rapports sociaux et de domination.
rien n’est visible ou invisible par essence. 
toute invisibilité ne relève pas de la non-existence mais bien d'une visibilité intentionnellement cachée, camouflée ou effacée.
.
.
pour le cahier central du numéro 4 de la revue, femmesphotographes, à lancé un appel à participation aux photographes souhaitant proposer une image en lien avec le mouvement #metoo.
.
@christine_delory_momberger écrit : « représenter la violence par le médium photographique demande de la “mettre en image”, de lui donner une forme propre, une force visuelle. actes de résistance, ces images soulèvent des émotions, touchent à de l’intime ou déclenchent des colères, quel que soit le choix fait par les photographes(...) »
.
.
.
.
.

text:
the nowhere girls by amy reed
genre - fiction, ya, fiercely feminist and anti-misogyny read it! 
style - follows multiple characters, our three heroines who fight against small town sexism (great to see diversity) and also has vignettes of other girls in the town and the online voice of toxic masculinity woven throughout 
high point - intersectional, sex positive feminism, how the three disparate girls we follow come together and bring others with them in their fight against entrenched sexism and rape culture 
low point - how women can be ground down - the no where girls refuse to be nobody and nowhere! 
take away - get angry, use that anger, transform it into power - girls you are not alone, boys be wonderful pieces of the solution (this book is so much more than i can say here)

text:
#whyididntreport #metoo 
because it started when i was 4, i didn't  understand what was happening, he bribed me with sweet biscuits and barbie doll clothes and when that didn't work he threatened to hurt my sister and said my family wouldn't believe me.. because i was ashamed, i felt tarnished, i didn't think anyone would love me if they knew that it happened, as if there was something i could have done to stop it? as if i allowed it to happen to me over and over again.. because of my age, the police couldn't do anything to charge him (i didn't know dates etc accurately enough for them, i was only a child) thankfully, my family believed me..
i found forgiveness many years ago, not for his sake but for mine. he holds no power over me anymore, my life will be forever changed by what he did, but his actions do not define me.. i hold the power.

i never thought the day would come that i would open up to social media about what he did to me, but by remaining silent, it feels like the shame is still eating away at me.. like after all these years he still hold a bit of the power through my silence.. i only hope that someone reading this who is struggling, can gain strength from knowing that you are not alone, you have a sister in me.
i see you, i hear you. 
you are valuable.  #believeher @whyididntreportit

text:
my little boy loves his toys, my little boy loves cuddles (tuggles) my little boy loves kisses, my little boy tells me when he’s upset, he’s not afraid to cry, he doesn’t see anything wrong in wearing his hair in a ponytail, he strokes me if he thinks i’m sad, he loves flowers, he loves animals, he loves his little mate beau.  each day i marvel but also feel pain at seeing him in his pure state.  i hope no one ever tells him that none of those attributes are not acceptable as a boy.  i hope his tears are never stifled by the words “man up”, i hope he always feels safe enough to express himself.  i hope he never has to hide behind a constructed gender norm.  i hope he realises there’s no such thing as being a “boy” or being a “girl” there’s just being you.  if you haven’t already read it, i’ve written a new blog post. link in bio ❤️
.
.

text:
#myreason
since the day she was born my world changed, i had purpose, a greater love than i could ever imagine. becoming a single mom and the losses and struggles we’ve been through were never part of my plan. i set out to be the best mother to my daughter from day one and despite these trials and tribulations that have been the most painful and difficult times, that hasn’t changed. in fact, through each obstacle i’ve only grown stronger, my reason, my purpose has become even more clear. i can teach my daughter through words or stories to be strong and confident and that she has a voice, she has rights and to stand up for them! but i don’t believe in words, to me they are empty promises w/o an action to back them up. words describe who you want to be or to be seen as, actions prove who and what you really are. i understand many out there don’t get or support that i’m a fighter, i don’t give up, despite how many times my hearts been shattered it still beats and i do all with my integrity, morals and values intact. it’s who i am, i’ve hated my heart for feeling so much, but if it didn’t i would have giving up long ago. i am a single mother, my daughter is my reason and my world, every decision i make is for her. her confidence, her smile, her happiness, despite the pains and years of this torture, show me that i’m making the right choices. how can i keep her feeling safe if i give up? teach her she has a voice, if i let them silence me? teach and show her her worth and the respect she deserves if i don’t fight for my own? she is my reason, my reason to get out of bed everyday despite the pain, my reason to smile, my reason to fight and the reason i will not give up, the reason we will win! i’m all she has to look up to right now, and every second of everyday goes into this battle, providing for her, caring for her, giving my all to make sure she can do what she loves in life, and any extra time i have is all for her! i may have no life anymore or time for anything else, but there is nothing more important to me than this beautiful, innocent soul and making sure she continues to feel safe, happy and loved every single day!

text: it really makes me more than severely anxious posting this, but for weeks i’ve been seeing how strong everyone is by sharing their traumatic experiences with being sexually assaulted.. i myself have not figured out a way to comfortably reach out to people for support that helps me specifically, but #metoo.. i am 100% there for anybody in similar situations and for anybody who needs positivity in their life. due to many different people’s assumptions and opinions of how such and such needs to be handled or dealt with... i’m scared. i am genuinely afraid to post and express my personal experiences of being sexually assaulted. many people might not believe me, mock me (@realdonaldtrump), or might not even understand, but it’s very, very real... and traumatic. my life has been completely turned upside down due to sexual abuse. my only purpose for sharing this post is in hope that at least one person will feel empowered enough to realize they aren’t alone, and to share their experiences and receive the justice they deserve.

text:
m e r c r e d i y
cette semaine, j'ai relevé le défi que m'a proposé @bostiksmartadhesives pour concevoir un diy en utilisant leur nouvelle colle réactive à la lumière, et j'en ai profité pour réaliser une suspension qui me faisait rêver depuis des lustres (sans mauvais jeu de mot 😇) : cette jolie suspension bohème en lin style koushi !
vous connaissez sûrement ces lampes vaporeuses, à la fois élégantes, authentiques et ethniques 🖤 je n'ai pas résisté à l'envie de m'en créer ma propre version avec des matériaux simples et naturels, je vous montre tout ça dans le tutoriel sur le blog !
•
et je vous propose même 2 versions de finition : dites moi laquelle vous préférez ! version 1 ou version 2 ?
•
et au fait, ne vous attachez pas trop à ce petit coin de la maison, il va changer de disposition, de couleur et de fonction très prochainement 🤗 la seule chose que je suis sûre de garder ? la suspension !

text:
!
🎀
🎀
una piccola polaroid di una piccola chiara dolce, felice e spensierata.
questa sono io.
in momenti come questi mando a fanculo i problemi, i brutti ricordi e chi ci sta intorno.
perché mi rendo conto di avere una famiglia e amici su cui posso contare realmente.
mi è stato detto di vivere in un mondo di favole. fortunatamente in questo mondo non ci vivo solo io, ma anche tante altre persone che la pensano come me e che schifano il mondo e il modo di pensare di tanti altri. 
non cadere mai ai piedi di chi ha bisogno di sminuirti per sentirsi migliore; conserva ogni cosa di te... l'ingenuità, le insicurezze, la timidezza e la fiducia nei sogni.
cresci..ma non cambiare.
🎀
🎀

text:
peace out lights in. taught 06.30 flow this morning, 19th class since #ohsytt2018 ended. the thought of me cuing asanas is a bit unreal but still it’s me walking around the room showing alignments, givning adjustments. loving the support from students showing up when it’s cold and dark outside. loving my willpower to be enough and loving the fear that i won’t be.
•
in all this brightness i also want to mention that i’m really relieved that the swedish man known as kulturprofilen got sentenced to two years in prison for rape. even though i’m against punishment as a lastning solution this is such an important confirmation for the victim and those who testified against this powerful man.
•

compassion !  i had the most amazing compliment yesterday: "that's not normal". was thrown out there in a conversation. to my "what's not normal ?" i was told "your compassion !" i'll save you from the long version, as it had to be repeated "oh a mere 3, 5 times +++" along with an inner movie of my life. (no we don't have to wait until we pop our clogs and become our full selves again, to have a life review. ( but thats a different topic :) ) ). the freedom of encompassing compassion fully is really beyond words. every aspect of everything in life is a choice.  i probably have more reason than most not to choose compassion. raped by a doctor age 4. 40 years later i finally walked away from the familiar slavery n more that (i allowed) because of the trauma and unrecognised "fear malware. " of it, and the silence and hiding by the supposed adults in my life. i have written about the near death experiences and unconditional love that made me remember my choice of real freedom and the choice of being compassion.  #metoo⁠ ⁠ more soon.  with love & grace m.  #heartcloudconsultants #solutiondetectives #holisticallyhappysolutions #holisticemotionalhealthandwellnesscoaching  #mindfulawareness
